<br>
As my father lost his vision, I took on the duties of making deliveries to Surefall Glade in his place.  This is how I came to know of the rangers.  Though completely blind now, my father is still a skilled craftsman and continues his trade.  Until now, it was my calling in life to assist him.<br>
<br>
However, with the new threat to Jaggedpine by the gnolls, I have pledged my life to assisting the rangers of Surefall Glade.  My sister takes my place at my father's side while I struggle to learn the ways of the ranger.  To attempt this new path at such an advanced age is a struggle, considering most that stand beside me are still children in the eyes of many.  However, my duty calls me, and I percevere despite the hardships.<br>
<br>
To those of you that also defend Surefall and the Qeynos area, I hail thee, and aspire to one day fight alongside against a common foe...<br>
<br>
(ooc) <br>
I just returned to Everquest after a long layoff that was the result of disillusionment from a complete lack of immersion.  When you feel like this game is a job, and your guild is an employer... something is terribly wrong.<br>
<br>
I came back hoping to feel like I was in a roleplaying game, not chasing a carrot.  Thus far, Firiona Vie has given me the canvas for this.  I am free to roleplay without people reacting to me like I have a mental defect, and everyone I have interacted with in game has been genuinely helpful.  I feel like I did after installing the game in 1999 and staring in wide eyed wonder at my monitor.<br>
<br>
Thanks to all of the kind people that have helped me learn the basics of the server.  I am loving the challenge of working my way from nothing, and having fun while I play rather than hoping it will get fun when I reach X level.<br>
<br>
Love your server, and I hope to someday become an established citizen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caemus>Caemus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/14/03 4:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=452.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First Steps</span><hr size=1> Hello, Rainwind.  I am Caemus.  I have recently relocated to the Glade from my home in the Greater Faydark for, well, reasons that are not altogether very pleasant for me to discuss at the moment.  However, I have found that the quiet solitude of the glade often leads me brooding over such unpleasantries and I feel a need to occupy myself with more constructive activities.  <br>
<br>
So, if you find yourself in need of a companion, one who is willing to lend his powers of healing, protecting or casting Tunare's fury against our common foes, feel free to call on me.  Even if I am not in the Glade at the time, I can reach it quickly.<br>
<br>
Until such time, safe journeys and may your endeavors be fruitful.<br>
